urlhtml: Rue de la Grange aux Belles, 8

title: Saint-Jacques Tower
description: This 52-m Gothic tower is all that remains of the former church of Saint-Jacques-la-Boucherie (Saint James of the Butchery). A statue of Blaise Pascal is located at the base of the tower, commemorating his experiments on atmospheric pressure performed here.
